 This is not a distribution yet; please do not redistribute.

Documentation will be forthcoming.  In the meantime:

The mtgl is a set of header files, so there's no installation. In order
to build some test programs, however, we do have a build process.

<ON THE MTA/XMT:    export CC=cc; export CXX=c++  >


autoreconf -i -f -s
./configure
make 

Some of the other tests cause internal 
compiler errors on the MTA/XMT when compiled separately (make-style), but
work when compiled all together on one command line.  See test/Makefile.am
for help with those.  We recommend starting with test_static_graph[123].


Notes for building on Macs OS 10.4:
Here is a system configuration that works for building MTGL:
  m4:  v1.4.10
  autoconf:  v2.61
  automake:  v1.10
Here is a system configuration that does NOT work:
  m4:  v1.4.2
  autoconf:  v2.59
  automake:  v1.6.3

Running:
-----------------------------------
n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> mtarun -m 1 ./test_static_graph1 
0: 1
1: 2
2: 0
-----------------------------------
n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> mtarun -m 1 ./test_static_graph2 10
-----------------------------------
n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> mtarun -m 1 ./test_static_graph3 10
-----------------------------------
n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test>  mtarun -m 1 ./cc_test
usage: ./cc_test [-debug]  [-bu | -cc | -ch | -sv]  --graph_type <mmap|dimacs|cray>  --level <levels> --graph <Cray graph number>  --filename <mmap|dimacs graph filename>  [<0..15>]
------------------------------------
n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> mtarun -m 10 ./cc_test -cc --graph_type rmat --graph_struct dyn --graph 15
			( -cc selects Kahan's algorithm
			  --graph_type rmat      generate r-mat graphs
			  --graph_struct dyn     store them in dynamic graph
						 data structure
			  --graph 10             2^10 vertices)
			The file "mtgl_test.h" contains the call to
			gen_rmat_graph, along with a non-exposed parameter
			selecting the average degree.
----------------------------------------
n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> c++ -I.. -par -pl test.pl -o test_community graph.cpp test_community.cpp ufl.cpp VolVolume.cpp -lm -lprand

n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> mtarun -m 10 ./test_community --graph_type rmat --graph_struct dyn --graph 10

---------------------------------------------
n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> mtarun -m 1 ./test_sssp
usage: ./test_sssp [-debug]  [-ds | -sssp_et]  --graph_type <mmap|dimacs|rmat> --graph_struct <dyn|static> --level <levels> --graph <SCALE> --filename <mmap|dimacs graph filename> --trials <#> --num_srcs <#> --vs <vsource>

n10790@mta-gate-linux:~/mtgl/test> mtarun -m 10 ./test_sssp -ds --graph_type rmat --graph_struct dyn --graph 10 --trials 10 --num_srcs 2

